OL,7,FOther UK collaborators include the
OL,8,FNational Centre for Earth Observation
OL,9,F(NCEO), the universities of Oxford and
OL,10,FLeicester, Imperial College and the
OL,11,FNational Centre for Atmospheric
OL,12,FScience.
OL,14,FOnce launched, EarthCARE will circle
OL,15,FEarth every 90 minutes at an altitude
OL,16,Fof around 400km (250 miles).
OL,18,FIt will cross the equator in the early
OL,19,Fafternoon to optimise daylight
OL,20,Fconditions, ESA said.
